  <problem>
    <title> Angular Acceleration </title>
    
      <p>A disc is spinning about an axis passing through its center perpendicular to the page. At t=0, the angular velocity of the disc is 20 rad/s and the disc is spinning counterclockwise. The disc slows down at a steady rate, and at t = 3.0 s its angular velocity is 8.0 rad/s; the disc is still spinning counterclockwise. The disc continues to slow down at the same rate until t = 12.0 s.
</p>
      <br/>
    
    <img width="492" alt="BK76" encrypturl="no" src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/Pictures/BK76.png"/>
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11"/>
    <br/>
    
